<subSubSection id="BC9778DCE47B18FC879AC6A6DF415675" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="types">
<paragraph id="E01C3DC3102884AE81D6F6FD4B1FA1E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Types.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AEE9EB501DC8C1D39025C7C7F9BD6D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C556AD987AE3488293B3D417C9A471CC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Holotype</emphasis>
♂ (TARI), Taiwan. Hualien: Hahuan Cross-Ridge (合歡越嶺古道), 4.VIII.2018, leg. H.-F. Lu. 
<emphasis id="84A8736EA8894FF907D851EF2F8303F5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="9C51480D83411D494E36F3A4B61205A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Paratypes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
16♂, 7♀ (TARI), same data as holotype; Hualien: 3♀ (TARI), Hutoushan (虎頭山), 21.IV.2018, leg. H.-F. Lu; Kaohsiung: 1♀ (TARI), Chungchihkuan (中之關), 17.IV.2012, leg. L.-P. Hsu; 4♂, 3♀ (TARI), same locality, 12.VI.2015, leg. C.-F. Lee; Miaoli: 1♂ (TARI), Hsuehchien (雪見), 7.VI.2013, leg. W.-B. Yeh; Nantou: 1♂ (TARI), Chingching (清境), 5.III.2007, leg. H.-C. Chen; 1♂ (TARI), Meifeng (梅峰), 2-4.VI.1980, leg. L. Y. Chou &amp; C. C. Chen; 1♀ (TARI), same locality, 24-26.VI.1981, leg. K. S. Lin &amp; W. S. Tang; 1♂ (TARI), Tatachia (塔塔加), leg. 21.VI.2009, leg. C.-F. Lee; Taichung: 1♂, 2♀ (TARI), Kukuan (谷關), 21.III.2014, leg. B.-X. Guo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1C2D5C064B5CD5C1B25E9CB1283F64E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="38C1EFACF63BE040502D7849186877DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C73778900D963F37E44BE28375153D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Elytra relatively narrow, 1.7-1.8 
<normalizedToken id="EA9D62587551873500EA65A2275A58B4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, entirely yellowish brown or black; disc smooth, lacking ridges; with sparse, fine punctures
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53AE2958F5B329EDA5FB439E43305E28" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="60CE4B1A789A26459EC8322BDAA83920" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84C8EA087F688C8DF74AA01454FA6665" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Length 4.6-5.3 mm, width 2.0-2.4 mm. Body yellow, head and pronotum reddish brown, antenna blackish brown except ventral sides of five basal antennomeres, bases of femora and lateral margins of tibia black; tarsi darker in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="238B284898E3D9C8BAB285A8E58921E4" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Habitus of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A male, typical form, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F male, color variation, dorsal view G ditto, ventral view H male, color variation, dorsal view I ditto, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545571" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41D, E</figureCitation>
); but head, scutellum, thoracic ventrites, and basal 2/3 of femora black in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="55E4DF1AB648BE3F29AA8816AF22396F" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Habitus of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A male, typical form, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D female, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F male, color variation, dorsal view G ditto, ventral view H male, color variation, dorsal view I ditto, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545571" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41A-C</figureCitation>
). Eyes small, interocular space 2.55-2.85 
<normalizedToken id="51BECF865BF354878227D27E3A9A2CB3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
diameter of eye. Antennae filiform in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3B7382EA62C9C4FF1F5EC2C0D57373CB" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42A</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.6: 0.8: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.8, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.6: 1.9: 2.5: 2.1: 2.2: 2.2: 2.4: 2.5: 2.8: 2.4: 2.9; similar in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AD66C7DCAC93AA408D8E1D53377220E6" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42B</figureCitation>
), length ratios of antennomeres I-XI 1.0: 0.6: 0.9: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.7: 0.9, length to width ratios of antennomeres I-XI 2.7: 2.1: 2.7: 2.2: 2.2: 2.2: 2.2: 2.1: 2.3: 2.1: 3.1. Pronotum and elytra convex. Pronotum 1.8-2.0 
<normalizedToken id="2C214F01F460138D05CDF5C1420C6926" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, with transverse ridge along apical margin deflexed at antero-lateral angles; disc smooth on ridge, but with reticulate microsculpture below ridge, with extremely coarse punctures laterally, smaller medially, with one short seta at each puncture; with median longitudinal and lateral depressions; lateral margins moderately rounded, widest at middle, apical and basal margins slightly concave; anterior and posterior setiferous punctures not erect. Elytra broad, parallel-sided, 1.7-1.8 
<normalizedToken id="51C165C226FCA8C2D61CD42782F1C6F2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; disc smooth, with dense, coarse punctures, and extremely dense, short pubescence, some located between punctures. Apical spur of tibia of middle leg absent and tarsomere I not modified in males. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4905FEAA232B8D1634CA8A11619C1C4B" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42C, D</figureCitation>
) slender in dorsal view, 6.3 
<normalizedToken id="B3B5EECED2BF8671FE76318E181FA503" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, asymmetrically lanceolate, slightly curved at middle, strongly narrower near apex, apex narrowly rounded; ostium obliquely longitudinal, covered by a membrane; strongly curved near base in lateral view, apex narrowly rounded; two endophallic sclerites elongate, primary sclerite 0.7 
<normalizedToken id="0A4430F3249C8525BE7BA2799E0B7D13" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as aedeagus, with dense teeth along apical margin. Secondary sclerite much shorter than primary sclerite, 0.6 
<normalizedToken id="93DE725FB573C28DEFAA9F7F272B0407" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as primary sclerite, apex acute. Only apices of gonocoxae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E75182EB373D8C19802BBD13733AE21C" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42I</figureCitation>
) sclerotized, longitudinal, few short setae near base, with eight to ten long setae near apex on each gonocoxa. Ventrite VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3D31DD2CF81BE7EC364C8A762630560F" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42E</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized, with dense short setae along lateral and apical area, with short and long marginal setae, spiculum long. Receptacle of spermatheca (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8DF86C5FA39A79CB833A1EA9E4F18349" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42F</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen and elongate; pump short and strongly curved; sclerotized proximal spermathecal duct narrow and short. Apical margin of abdominal ventrite V slightly concave medially and with deep depression in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="103F838CBD052792B9A6B164DE99EB1B" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42H</figureCitation>
); broadly rounded in females (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E356E9D5684801E00B9D28F1555FEFE3" captionStart="Figure 42" captionStartId="F42" captionText="Figure 42. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta lui sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545572" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">42G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
